>    - *Join by Dial-In*: Dial +1 347-480-3601 and enter this PIN: 645 195
>    700# (end with pound symbol "#"). To UNMUTE yourself to speak: dial *6
>    (star-6).
>
> *Following Up on Action 1: Report "We Have No Super!" to 311*
>
>    - Please tell us if you reported to 311
>    <https://forms.gle/kWnCGD3WCiA6q2K29>, or if you tried to, so that we
>    have a count. And thank you!
>    - If you didn't report, you can still do it this weekend. Here's how.
>    <http://bit.ly/wheresmysuper>
>    - Some people told us that they could not report anonymously. Don't do
>    anything you are uncomfortable with. PS -- If your 311 operator is only
>    asking for a phone number, you can create a free new phone number through Google
>    Voice <http://voice.google.com>. Here's how.
>    <https://www.dailydot.com/debug/google-voice-number/>
>    - Good news: A code compliance inspector was spotted in the courtyard
>    this week shortly after our 311 action.
>
> *Coming Soon... Action 2: Reporting Repair Complaints to Management*
>
>    - All tenants should: 1) fill out a tenant repair complaint checklist
>    and 2) review our letter to management. By *Saturday, May 9*, we will
>    email the documents and give printed copies to anyone who needs one. Please
>    complete by *Monday, May 11*. More details to come.
>
> *In other news:*
>
>    - *We're in contact with almost 80% of our tenants. *Help us reach the
>    last 10 apartments
>    <https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1MV_IHl6C0BbBv0W-ZGapodtX0nl6rnEFcXISVd5n0-A/edit?usp=sharing>.
>    If you know for a fact that they are vacant, please tell us.
>    - *The road ahead:* We now have a public timeline
>    <https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Aiv-Wz2QUm2mQv3C4Qc5ASnDv1GX2lO40TOmlxr2K9I/edit?usp=sharing> of
>    our tenant association's current and future projects. We need your help to
>    make it all happen.
>    - *Tenants all over NYC are on rent strike to #CancelRent. *As
>    unemployment reaches new highs due to COVID-19, nearly one third
>    of Americans did not pay rent in April. Thousands of tenants across NYC are not
>    paying rent
>    <https://gothamist.com/news/thousands-nyc-tenants-kick-historic-rent-strike-distressing-landlords>, out
>    of necessity or in solidarity with others, to create pressure on landlords
>    and government to provide rent relief.
>    Due to COVID, *some of our tenants were not able to pay rent in April*,
>    and many others need rent relief soon. Management has been unresponsive to
>    tenants' requests for rent payment plans and rent reductions. We plan to
>    survey all tenants on their willingness to participate in a rent strike and
>    other strategies to request rent relief (such as a letter).
>    - *All voters can now ask to vote by mail*: Request an absentee ballot
>    <https://nycabsentee.com/absentee> to vote in the June 23 elections.
>    Even if you aren't sick, it is now legal <https://nycabsentee.com/> to
>    select "Temporary illness" as your reason for requesting an absentee
>    ballot, to avoid catching COVID-19.
>
> Cheers,
> Your neighbors
> Hayes Court United
>
